  <h2>When to use link icons</h2>
  <p>Use link icons when a prominent text link needs a clear directional cue, such as going back or opening something externally.</p>
  <p>The canonical link icon component supports left and right icon positions so teams can keep the same underlying pattern for back links and outward links.</p>

  <h2>How to use link icons</h2>
  <p>Keep the text short and specific. Use a left icon for back-navigation style links and a right icon for external or forward-moving links.</p>
  <p>Choose the small size for compact inline usage and the medium size when the link needs more visual emphasis.</p>

  <h3>Accessibility</h3>
  <p>Make sure the text still describes the action on its own. The icon should support the message, not replace it.</p>

